translation:
One should always follow the conduct of a guru. In dealings with the guru's children and disciples, as well as with one's own relatives;
A child, whether by birth or by adoption, or even a student, should serve the son of his guru. The respect due to a guru is owed to his son as well.
Just as a man achieves fame through (the performance of) ritual offerings to fire, so also does one attain knowledge by serving the guru's lineage.

"Gathering hymn by Āngiras, Agni is the name, in anuṣṭubh and triṣṭubh meter;
You gather all, you illuminate for Vṛṣaṇna, for Dyuvasu; as Ilaspade you shine forth, be gracious to us with your blessings of the Vasus.
Gather together, converse together, let your thoughts be harmonious and become known to each other;
As the gods in ancient times gathered and assembled, thus let them approach us with good fortune.
The samāna mantra: unification, harmonious is samānī, samānaṃ is the mind; saha is the best portion;
With this samāna mantra I offer my oblations to you;
Unification is the call, unification is the insight, harmonious are the feelings within you;
May unity be in your mind, as it is beneficial for us. May there be good fortune."
